<br>
Not true.<br>
<br>
I can zone into Charsis and pull anyone of the 8 Golems, which are paired on each wing, with a single nuke.  All of the golems are blue to me.  A lower level member cannot.<br>
<br>
In Sebilis, I can pull a lot of singles that lower level members cannot and they are blue to me.  Kunark has different rules and it's not always as simple as that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=feaglund>Feaglund</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(11/1/00 8:10:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pulling With Nullify (Part 2)</span><hr size=1> That's very true.. The assist radius of a mob shrinks as you grow in levels relative to it. The same is true of agro radius, as the mob gets greener and greener to you, you can get closer and closer to it without agroing it, until its finally so low green that it never agros (except for certain types of mobs which are always agressive).<br>
<br>
So in your example the golems are spaced widely enough that their assist radii don't overlap. Another person, lower leveled than you, may not be able to do the same thing.<br>
<br>
'Pulling' refers to putting oneself on the hate list of a mob so that it pursues. The problem is that mobs that are in assist radius of each other are constantly sharing their hate lists with each other (i.e. if you are on one mob's hate list it will share you with the other mob and you'll be on both hate lists). Nullify is an offensive spell (i.e. it generates hate). I don't know of any other case where a spell can generate hate that isn't sharable. In other words, hate is hate, and it shouldn't really matter what spell you used to put yourself on the hate list, once you're on it you'll get added to other mobs within assist radius.<br>
<br>
There are some caveats to the above. There are mobs which simply don't assist each other. Usually this is a case of 2 mobs of different races (i.e. the goblins in frontier mts. never assist the other types of mobs in that zone, but the burynai do). Also, there are some strange cases where pathing prevents mobs from assisting. A simplistic case is the gnolls in Highpass. If you're on the ledge you can fight gnolls and the gnolls below won't assist.<br>
<br>
I believe many of the examples of Nullify pulling single mobs are really a case of the level difference of the puller, or strange pathing issue which is preventing mobs from assisting. Level difference is a well known factor in pulling. Level 55 pullers can pull most of Karnors solo, Level 60 pullers can pull dars and jin solo in Sebelis.<br>
<br>
The Bard song Kellin's Lugubrious Lament is an interesting tool, it reduces the assist radius of a mob so that a Bard can Lament the mobs around a mob and then pull the mob. In an xp camp Bards who know how to use this tool make excellent pullers because they can break a room of up to 4 mobs with that song.<br>
 <p><br>Feaglund
